  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the mother was killed by the Germans during the war, as was my father's sister, sister-in-law, all, all, all family.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The all family that they had in Poland was killed during the war.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My grandfather was the, I think, the what we see were paterfamilias.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was the, the boss of the family.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Well, each his word was law for the rest of the family.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was a traditional.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was Orthodox.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My most beautiful memories I have from the [NON-ENGLISH] that we had, either Pesach or Rosh Hashanah, or, or Yom Kippur, it was wonderful to be part of all this ritual.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "All that-- those blessings that I used to get, I always was sure that when I am under my grandfather's prayer shawl and he blesses me that somebody upstairs, that God upstairs blesses me.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He was a, a very imposing personality by his will and by his thoughts.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It is funny when you ask me now, I sometimes think when I-- we sit on a Friday night and the family is all together and my grandchildren make [INAUDIBLE], I sometimes think that I wish my, my grandfather somewhere would see that his ways are not cut off, that we are going in his ways, and, and that I'm a good girl, that I'm bringing them up Jewish-- not only my children, but my grandchildren, too.",
      "word_count": 77
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And that would please him.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Because it meant for him his religion and all that culture meant so much for him.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "That for us basically, as we say in Hebrew, [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "That was his way of living and that he instilled of us-- and he always talked that when we grow up, that we have to go in the same path.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
